# Spec2Test Notices

Spec2Test is an Open Plugin Beta distribution for PerfectOne-based C unit
verification workflows.

The repository intentionally excludes PerfectOne CLI binaries and PerfectOne
engine source code. Users must provide a compatible `ClangParserForWin.exe`
or platform-specific PerfectOne CLI binary separately.

`samples/c-input04-complex/sample1.c` is included as a user-provided complex C
stress sample derived from `C:\Development\TestSuite\input04\input04.c`.
The file is included for beta evaluation and regression testing of C coverage,
residual harness generation, UB/ASAN reporting, and HTML report generation.

The beta is focused on Windows C workflows:

- Docker runs source-target filtered KLEE baseline execution.
- Windows LLVM/lld-link runs local residual native replay and MC/DC coverage.
- WSL execution is disabled for this plugin path.
- Non-C workflows are temporarily disabled in this beta plugin deployment.
- Embedded C workflows are not validated yet and require explicit target
  compiler, sysroot, linker, and build context before any execution.
